description: Collects : X-Factor (2006) # 201 - New Mutants (2009) # 08,11 - X-Force (2008) # 23
name: X-Necrosha parte 6 di 9

description: Collects : X-Factor (2006) # 202 - New Mutants (2009) # 09 - X-Force (2008) # 24
name: X-Necrosha parte 8 di 9

description: Collects : X-Factor (2006) # 203 - New Mutants (2009) # 10 - X-Force (2008) # 25 - X-Necrosha - Dazzler (2010)
name: X-Necrosha parte 9 di 9

description:
A new wave of crimes has fallen on East City : a mysterious serial killer kills, leaving on body of its prey a small necklace of jade that ressemble a cicada. Nathan Never Is in charge of the investigations, He understands from the first moment that  will not be easy to get to the bottom of the case. 

Even with the help of the psychic Katja Claussen, a woman with incredible ESP powers  which allows her to revive in first hand the tragic last life's moments  of the victims.

And while the murderess, who seems to be able to prevent every move of   our hero  , continues to kill, Katya is forced to experience more suffering ...
name: La Cognizione Del Dolore

description: Collects : X-Factor (2006) # 204 - X-Force (2008) # 26 - Uncanny X-Men (1981) # 524 - X-Men Legacy (2008) # 235
name: Secondo Avvento : capitolo 3 (di 7)

description:
The end of the war led to a fragile balance of power.This balance is not only political but very huge Economic interests are related to the relations between the two opposite sides.

For this reason a  proposals of Distension by the Councillor Joan Grant are not frowned upon by  the economic lobbies of the earth planet, which helped by the fringes of the extremist separatist faction, decreed the elimination of the counselor.

Nathan is then sent under cover to Melpomene, with the task of infiltrating the subversive circles. The only clue he can count on, however, is the name of a shady individual, the person who could have provided to the killer the weapon with which he make the attempt ...
name: Mandato per un Omicidio

description: Collects : X-Factor (2006) # 205 - X-Force (2008) # 27 - Uncanny X-Men (1981) # 525 - X-Men : Hellbound (2010) # 01
name: Secondo Avvento : capitolo 5 (di 7)

description:
Net-Live is a virtual community that offers to its subscribers a peaceful environment for recreation, to relax, listen  good music and meet new people.

It is in this world who Patricia meets Will, in a short time they start a true love story, without  having ever seen each others in person.

When Will suddenly disappears without a trace, Patricia does not want lose her lover and  she decide to request the Agency for investigation. Nathan will be forced to dive into cyberspace to find clues that may lead him  to the real identity of Will, but in doing so he  discover that Net-Live is not exactly a paradise.
name: Il Segreto dei Numeri Primi

description:
Allied with Orange The Crime Lady of Sub City, Nathan and Nicole, along the labyrinth of the underground citadel, accidentally came across a mysterious physical phenomenon: a space-time anomaly.

The gate seems to be able to connect East City with a possible past of the U.S. of the Fifties ... At this point, it is important to understand how to control the phenomenon, and especially those who must manage it ...
name: Nelle Mani Dell'Assassino

description: Collects : X-Factor (2006) # 206 - X-Men : Hellbound (2010) # 02,03 -X-Men: Second Coming (2010) #02
name: Secondo Avvento : capitolo 7 (di 7)

description:
When a group of teens become the latest victims of the House of Liddle, a brilliant young boy will make it his personal mission to insure that the house never hurts anyone else again. But does the boy have what it takes to stop the house where madness lives and no one gets out alive? Don't miss this final chapter of the House of Liddle!

MATURE READERS

Note: The cover is an homage to movie The Shining.
name: The 2011 Wonderland Annual

description:
There is something  that vexes  Nathan , a worm  that gnaws at  his soul :  Special Agent  Alfa  number  2 decides to  deal with it,  and so penetrates  down  into the bowels  of the old  Alpha  Building to  confront the  puppeteer who  has  moved  the wires  of the Agency,  so as to  find out the secrets of  Mr.  Alpha.  
Nathan discovers that the main events that have  shaped the  recent history  of the agency and  the city ,  from the creation  of the breed  of the shifts  to the success  of the religious movement  of the Divine  Presence  of Reverend Skotos  up  to the situation  of tension between  the Earth and  the colonies  is about to  escalate into  war,  were  all  orchestrated  by the same hand, that of the enigmatic Chinese crimelord.
name: La vera storia di Mister Alfa

description: Three complete stories in this issue! "A Puzzle called Charlie" where Charlie is examined by University lab tech's to explore his "break-apart" abilities and the fun that ensues. "The Boring Captain Yawn" how do you defeat a villain whose ability makes you fall instantly to sleep as soon as you see him? "Mr. Jigsaw's Secret Love Child" is the cover story and a fun, all-ages romp in what happens when an innocent situation gets blown out of proportion.
name: A Puzzle called Charlie; The Boring Captain Yawn; Mr. Jigsaw's Secret Love Child

description: The solar system is on the brink of civil war. The first blood is shed and the crisis now seems irreversible. But not everything is as it seems, and to bring to light the dark plots that move the pieces on the board, a group of men ready for anything is going to make an assault on a secret base hidden in the mountains.
name: Il nido delle aquile

description: Following the shocking turn of events from last issue, abandoned by her allies and friends, Vampirella seeks comfort in the arms of Chaos' most infamous servant, Ethan Shroud. But as Pendragon, Brittney and the newly convened Scarlet Legion race to recover the next fragment of "The Crimson Codices," Vampirella quickly finds her worst fears realized. Lost, hunted and backed into a corner alone, will she fight to clear her name or merely embrace her dark destiny? Bet on a fight!
From Nathan's past  his old friend  Johnny  Stockhausen  bursts in to  bring  the  Alfa  agent  to one of the  toughest tests  of his life  ..
name: Ombre dal passato

description:
To advance in the the inquiry about the " berserker", a drug that can dramatically increase muscle strength and aggressiveness of the user the Alpha Agency join forces with Orange, a woman that shares with "The King" the control of the organised crime in Sub City. The pact is simple: Orange agree that the "berserker" won't go beyond the boundaries of the citadel of Sub City, and Nathan and Nicole will help Emma and Ray, the two henchmen of Orange, to find Baby, a dangerous fighter out of control.

Meanwhile, in New York in the Fifties (of the twentieth century), a stunned John Winter is about to finally be face to face with the mysterious serial killer known as "the Ogre" ...
name: Il Mistero Di Sub City

description: The murder of  a programmer, July   Hanecke ,  throws  the   Alfa  Agency  in a paradoxical situation :  while the  cameras  have filmed the victim in a hotel with his  murder ,  a man ,  in fact,  all indications  show  the presence of  a woman ,  that  could never  be in  that place  ...
name: Vita artificiale

description: SPINNING OUT OF WORLD WAR HULKS! THE SENSATIONAL SHE-HULK RETURNS! Jen Walters teams up with LYRA, the all-new SAVAGE SHE-HULK, to bring the hurt down on the fugitive members of THE INTELLIGENCIA. Klaw, Mad Thinker, Red Ghost, Trapster, and Wizard tried to take over the world and now must pay for what they've done. Plus: You NEVER ask a woman her age - especially when she can bench press tractor trailers! But She-Hulk's big secret is out: Marvel's celebrating 30 years of the Jade Giantess, and you're invited to the party! Join acclaimed Shulkie scribe Peter David for an anniversary tale unlike any other! Collecting SHE-HULKS #1-4, material from SHE-HULK SENSATIONAL #1, and handbook entries for both the Sensational and Savage She-Hulks.
name: TPB

description: Jeremy Sikes is a former motor racing champion, now a smuggler of illegal technology on the dusty streets of the "Territory". His accomplice, Arthur Lizbauer, subtracts some prototypes from Kobayashi Corp., the "zaibatsu" he works for.  Nathan, appointed to investigate the theft, locates him and soon the two become  friends. But Yakuza is also on his trail... Meanwhile, the  ambitious Pamela Tushingham of " Channel Death"  (a TV network dedicated to the most unscrupulous "truth chronicle") wants to make a documentary about Sikes life.
name: Piste infuocate

description:
Urania 's really fall! The giant cylinder of iron and steel has suddenly reappeared in the sky above East City and collapsed to the ground , causing millions of victims , giving the final blow to a city already in agony.

The world of the Special Agent Never has never seemed so dark and hopeless, a wounded world who still wonder why all these deaths and clings to the hope of finding survivors under the rubble ...
name: La Vita Oltre La Vita

description:
Inside Urania, the immense space station fallen inexplicably over the City, the security corps of the Proconsuls has documented an incredible flood of people ... these people have decided to defy the law and the ban from entering the structure, because of a sort of pilgrimage for the hope in the redemption of their sins and in order to heal their illness.

But in the footage of the piligrimage shot by the Proconsuls, Nathan recognizes something familiar in a person that stands aloof, a man covered in bandages, which should not be there, that should not even be alive ...

Nathan Ignore the orders of the director Solomon Darver ,and he decides to penetrate the wreck of Urania to give an answer to is questions about that man , to clarify their doubts, but most of all in order to obtain a long-dreamed revenge.

In this issue Nathan finally can take revenge on Havilland his ex colleague , the murderess of his ex-lover Hadija.

Nathan after a short fight is able to kill Havilland ,already on the verge of death for a terrible illnes , but he is immediatly resurrect and healed by the ghost of Luke Sanders.

Never is angry and amazed by that but the ghost justifies itself ,saying that the Nathan that He knew when he was alredy alive would not have ever done .

Luke says that in order to bring back Nathan on the path of the moral correctness from time lost because of the events of the war.

One of the Final scenes of the issue shows Nathan that visiting the grave of Luke and his companions died during the war.

This number concludes also the saga "Spazio-Temporale" , started with the issue n. 194 "Le Strade di New York".
name: La Vendetta

description: Väinämöinen becomes a radio-person, a video-game based on him is made, Seppo Ilmarinen Jr. creates a truth machine, Jabe becomes a rapstar, and they visit Europe again. The last book in the series.
name: Joka vanhoja muistaa.../That who remembers the old...

description:
Strange meteors start to land on Earth. Mojo Jojo takes notice and brings his monkey army to investigate. The meteors release small monsters that attack the KND treehouse and Foster's Home for Imaginary Friends. The treehouse is overrun, but Numbuh 2 and Numbuh 5 are saved by Blossom and Bubbles (Buttercup has recently gone missing). They are then saved by Dexter and Ben.

Later, the heroes all meet to coordinate their defensive strategy. Dexter and the Professor tell the others they can build the Electro-Pulse Cannon. Dexter says the only way they can accomplish this is if they team up. The others are reluctant, but Mac is able to convince them. However, the two final components needed are in Mojo's volcano and Mandark's fortress.

Blossom, Bubbles, Numbuh 2 and Ben go to Mojo's volcano. They encounter the alien monsters, but escape with the part they need. Meanwhile, Numbuh 5 leads Mac, Bloo, and Dexter's sister Dee-Dee to Mandark's fortress. He doesn't want to give them the part, but is easily persuaded through his infatuation with Dee Dee. However, he says he'll only give them the part if he's allowed to go with them.

Dexter is reluctant to side with Mandark, but realizes he must to save the world. While the EPC is powering up, their base is attacked by the alien monsters. The heroes fight back. They destroy the alien pod, but not before it fires a blast into space. Believing they've won, the heroes celebrate. However, a badly beaten Mojo lands near them. A large composite planet appears in the sky. Mojo explains that the blast was a beacon and Planet Fusion has arrived.
name: Fusionfall

description:
DOCTOR WHO MAGAZINE celebrates the life of NICHOLAS COURTNEY in a special 100-page bumper issue, packed with rare and never-before-published photos, dedicated to the man who played Brigadier Lethbridge-Stewart for over 40 years. Among those paying tribute to the actor who played the Doctor’s most trusted friend are former Doctors TOM BAKER, DAVID TENNANT, SYLVESTER McCOY and COLIN BAKER.

“Once you got to know Nick, you loved everything about him,” Tom explains to DWM. “We were a double act. I loved everything he did. I would have loved him as Othello. All other critical faculties were abandoned. You just couldn’t explain yourself. It was almost like someone saying, ‘What an Earth do you see in her?’ or ‘What on Earth do you see in him?’ Once you actually love someone, you just love being with them – and Iloved being with Nick.”

ALSO THIS ISSUE:

SALUTING THE BRIG NICHOLAS PEGG sets the scene as friends and colleagues remember the life and times of Nicholas Courtney. The tributes include contributions from FRAZER HINES, WENDY PADBURY, PETER PURVES, JOHN LEVENE, RICHARD FRANKLIN, KATY MANNING, RUSSELL T DAVIES, DERRICK SHERWIN, TERRANCE DICKS, PHILIP HINCHLIFFE, GRAEME HARPER and many more.

NICHOLAS COURNEY – A LIFE IN ACTING
DWM looks back at Nick’s long career, from his early days in rep through to his most famous role as Lethbridge-Stewart in Doctor Who and The Sarah Jane Adventures.

THE ONE WITH THE EYEPATCH Nicholas Courtney’s favourite Doctor Who story, 1970’s INFERNO, is put under the spotlight as THE FACT OF FICTION witnesses the end of the world…

SEVENTH HEAVEN It was the season in which the Brig came into his own – the Third Doctor’s first series from 1970. DWMlooks back to discover what made the season so special as COUNTDOWN TO 50 continues.

THE BRIG VS THE DOCTOR The Brigadier’s decision to blow up the reptile people in 1970’s Doctor Who and the Silurians shocked the Third Doctor. But was Lethbridge-Stewart right to do what he did? TOBY HADOKE and JOHNNY CANDON discuss the pros and cons of the Brig’s most controversial action in A BATTLE OF WITS…

NUNS WITH GUNS! The Doctor and Amy are shocked to find that the TARDIS has been harbouring a terrifying secret in the latest comic strip adventure! And there are more surprises in store in Part Two of APOTHEOSIS, written by JONATHAN MORRIS with art by DAN McDAID…

GAME ON! THE TIME TEAM continues its mission to watch every episode of Doctor Who in order, and visit the year 200,000 – but what will Chris, Emma, Michael and Will make of the Ninth Doctor adventure, THE LONG GAME?

ARE YOU MY MUMMY? The secret’s out! In an exclusive interview, actor ALEX KINGSTON talks about the revelation of just who River Song really is – and what the astonishing news means for her character in future episodes ofDoctor Who…

IT’S A MIRACLE! TORCHWOOD, the popular spin-off from Doctor Who, returns to TV in July with a 10-part story, MIRACLE DAY. DWM catches with writer RUSSELL T DAVIES and stars JOHN BARROWMAN, EVE MYLES and KAI OWEN to find out more abut the new series…

SPLENDID CHAP... An ancient power makes an unexpected return from the depths of the void and discovers a world very different to the one it left some time ago... Whatever you do, don’t miss PRODUCTION NOTES!

WOTCHA, BRIG! The Watcher dons his eyepatch and reveals some of the surprising lesser-known facts about everyone’s favourite UNIT commander in WOTCHA!

PLUS!

All the latest official news, reviews of TV and merchandise reviews, previews, competitions, a prize-winning crossword and much, much more!

Features the comic strip:

Apotheosis, part 2 by Jonathan Morris and Dan McDaid.
name: Apotheosis, part 2

description:
Nadia  Galya ,  President  of the Security Council and  the Alpha Agency's  valuable  ally ,  was  one of the victims  of the crash  of the  Urania  station  on the  City .
Now the Council  is  being reorganized  and Solomon Darver  is anxious to  renew his  useful  contacts  with his  new management team .   
For  this reason, He  accept  a dangerous mission and He  sends  a group of his  agents  to Mars to  capture Jack  Gordon ,  a former  colonel that   has turned is back to   the army and now  is leading a  private war against  the  corporations that  are taking care  of the  terraforming of   the  Red Planet  ...
name: La Giungla Di Marte

description:
While investigating  about  some mysterious  physical phenomena that  are occurring  in an are   of East City ,  Nathan  was hit by  a wave of  energy that  teleports him to  thousands  of miles  from Earth . 
Together with him  are "captured "  some boys  of two  opposing  street gangs ,   the " neo-Templarism" and the "  Hoplites" ,  both  leded by  powerful "T ecnopati" .   
Nathan  will have to find  a way to  back  home and  at the same time ,  prevent that  the tension between  the two  gangs  leads to a  vicious  bloodbath  ...
name: Sfida Dell'Ignoto

description: As Thor battles the nigh unstoppable Destroyer, a heroic mortal by the name Jake Wilson is accidentally killed. To atone for this injustice, the God of Thunder is bonded with this mortal's soul to set the wrong things right.Collects Thor (1998) #1-2.
name: Thor: Resurrection

description: Collects Uncanny X-Men #279, Wolverine (1988) #77-78, and X-Men (1990) #33.
name: The Art of Adam and Andy Kubert

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: In this special volume, Claremont chooses his favorite stories that he felt were the high-water marks in his long tenure on Marvel's Merry Mutants. Featuring artwork from some of the greats in the comics medium, the adventures in this collection cover all genres, from straightforward super-hero action, to whimsical fairy tales, to taut tales of espionage. Collects Uncanny X-Men #114,153, 186, 198, 268, Kitty Pryde & Wolverine #4, New Mutants (Vol. 1) #45, and Excalibur (Vol. 1) #16.
name: X-Men Visionaries: Chris Claremont

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description:
In New York in the Fifties, John Winter, a police officer and a veteran of the Second World War with a special "sixth sense", is called to solve the case of a serial killer who terrorizing the city. Meanwhile, in the future, Nathan Never and his colleagues are involved in the hunt of two dangerous criminals that are under the lead of Orange, cynical and ruthless new lady of Sub City, the citadel of the crime.

But how the New York of John Winter in the past is connected to the megalopolis of the future ?

The answer is hidden somewhere in the basement of Sub City ...

With this issue starts also the saga "Spazio- Temporale".
name: Le strade di New York

description: Modern day legend Jim Lee brings his brand of action adventure to Marvel's Merry Mutants. In this collection of some of his earliest, and critically accalimed, work Lee captures the imagination of a legion of fans. The X-Men encounter alien Skrulls and bumo into the Shi'ar for their seemingly annual throw-down. Plus, Wolverine has a decades spanniung adventure with Captain America in WWII and Black Widow in modern day. Plus, who could forget Rogue and Magneto's sultry adventure in the Savage Land. Collects Uncanny X-Men #248, 256-258, 268-269, and 273-277.
name: X-Men Visionaries: Jim Lee

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: A powerhouse collection of the most popular heroes drawn by one of the decade's most popular artists! From John Byrne to Marc Silvestri, from John Romita Jr. to Jim Lee, many creators have leapt into the spotlight with their work on Uncanny X-Men. Following this path to success, Joe Madureira exploded onto the scene in 1994, with a look heavily influenced by the Japanese manga style. Fans immediately responded to this newcomer's clean yet turbo-charged look at Marvel's mutant heroes. Collected here are some of the finest examples of his innovative work, as the Children of the Atom race from the Morlock Tunnels to Hong Kong to outer space on their never-ending fight for peace. Includes Uncanny X-Men #325 (guest-starring Callisto and Spider-Man), #329-330 (the martial arts masterpiece entitled 'The Quest of the Crimson Dawn'), #341-343 (featuring the Shi'Ar and the parasitic Phalanx) and the double-sized 350th issue, featuring the infamous 'Trial of Gambit!' Collects Uncanny X-Men #325-326, 328-330, 340-343, 345, and 350.
name: X-Men Visionaries: Joe Madureira

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: The Legion of Super-Heroes finds itself stranded in a distant galaxy, on the home planet of the vicious alien race known as the Progeny, in this new hardcover collecting the cult favorite 12-issue epic. While some of our heroes struggle to repair their damaged spaceship, the rest attempt to forge an alliance with the peaceful Kwai. But can the Legion help the Kwai defeat their oppressors and still make their way back home to Earth?
name: Legion Lost

description: From the books by Edgar Rice Burroughs that was made up of a collection of short stories about the adventures of Tarzan as a boy before he had Jane and other from civilization.
name: The Beasts of Tarzan

description:
Jack, the son of Tarzan and Jane leave London with a ape named Akut in order to regive him his freedom. Now named Korak by the ape tribe, he learn to live in jungle.

He save Meriem, a young slave woman, and, after many adventures, marry her.
name: The Son of Tarzan

description: It's a super-villain team-up unlike anything ever seen in a comicbook before! And it's the worst possible timing for Butcher, who's balls-deep inside some serious superheroine cushioning, desperately trying to prove his manhood! But that's just the sauce... read it for the pasta, too! So let's rock out with our c**ks out!

Following the phenomenal success of Marvel Comics #1, Timely released its second superhero anthology Daring Mystery Comics, in January 1940. This hardcover collection remasters and restores these early adventures that introduce brand-new characters into the Marvel mythos (several of whom will be appearing in The Twelve by J. Michael Straczynski & Chris Weston). See the startling introduction of the Fiery Mask where he faces the fantastic thriller of the walking corpses. Soldier of fortune John Steel sneaks behind enemy lines. The Phantom Bullet, scourge of the underworld, faces off against a dastardly band of Head Hunters. District Attorney Dennis Burton decides to take the law into his own hands as the Laughing Mask and then later as the Purple Mask. Meet the Phantom Reporter – cub reporter by day…scourge of the underworld by night. Plus: The Texas Kid; Monako, Prince of Magic; Flash Foster, Phantom of the Underworld, Barney Mullen, Sea Rover; Zephyr Jones and his rocket ship; Trojak the Tiger Man; Captain K-4 and his Sky Devils; Mr. E; Dale of the FBI; Breeze Barton in the Miracle City; Marvex the Super-Robot; Captain Strong of the Foreign Legion; Whirlwind Carte of the Interplanetary Secret Service; and more!

Reprints "Daring Mystery Comics" #1-4
name: The Fantastic Thriller of the Walking Corpses

volume.name: Marvel Masterworks: Golden Age Daring Mystery

description:
There's no age like the Golden Age! Timely Comics' second, sensational comic book series started off with an eclectic array of heroes and artistic talents that mixed pulp rawness with the exploding energy of the comic book medium. Now, with a fix on the new field, DARING MYSTERY COMICS brings in the big guns and lets loose! Featuring a who's who of Golden Age talent, these stories are a rollicking ride through the frenetic era that gave birth to America's greatest fictional creation, the super hero. Joe Simon and Jack Kirby bring you the original Marvel Boy, the 31st century space opera of Captain Daring, and the Fiery Mask. Bill Everett, master of the maritime hero, creates The Fin-Robin Hood of the Seas. Carl Burgos's Thunderer debuts as the powerhouse of justice. Ben Thompson unleashes the Blue Diamond, bullet-proof man. Harry Sahle introduces the super heroine Silver Scorpion. And Citizen V battles his way across war-torn Europe for victory! Also featuring Dynaman, Trojak the Tiger Man, K-4 and His Sky Devils, Monako Prince of Magic, Marvex the Super Robot, Breeze Barton, Stuporman, the Flying Flame and Mr. Million, DARING MYSTERY COMICS is a cornucopia of action and adventure! Collecting DARING MYSTERY COMICS #5-8.

Reprints "Daring Mystery Comics" #5-8.
name: The Jelly of Doom

volume.name: Marvel Masterworks: Golden Age Daring Mystery

description: Nicole  Bayeux , the newest agent of the Alfa Agency, receives a call  from his father whom she thought dead ... While in  the shadows  new, dangerous enemies are about to come out.
name: Nicole Bayeux, agente Alfa

description: The saga " Spazio-Temporale" continues ; t he world of the past at the end irrimediably meets that of the future ! But the consequences of this event have gone far beyond what Nathan Never and all the members of the Agency Alfa could think about ... An unprecedented disaster will hit everyone, all life will be marked indelibly by this experience ...
name: Quando La Città Muore

description:
Nathan Never is entrusted with ( what looks like) a routine mission : he is charged to escort   Herbert Katyn , a diplomat of the space station in  visit to East City for a series of conferences . 
Instead , our Special Agent Alfa will be thrown into an abyss of horror. Katyn will be threatened of death by the young and implacable Maori Asjia , that Nathan had met in a previous mission and with whom he had had a brief but intense love affair .
Revenge is the spring that pushes Asjia to act : the man who protects Nathan is guilty , he said , of horrendous crimes . But what is the truth?
name: il carnefice

description: Surprised by killers Leonid and Ash while on a mission to protect political candidate John Cleverly Cartney, Nathan wakes up after two weeks and found to be wanted by police for a triple murder, which, however, he does not remember to have committed. Only because of his friends of the Alfa Agency, he can take refuge in a safe place. But there is someone among people who know of his hiding place that doesn’t seem willing to protect the agent Never.
name: Nemico pubblico

description: Nathan is in jail, awaiting a terrible sentence, but his friends at Alfa Agency do not stand with folded hands and organize a spectacular escape. Alone and hunted by all, Nathan finds refuge in Midian, a sort of “Court of Miracles” located in the basement of the city, the only place where the outcast as he is can hide. And here our hero will meet two old friends: Angel de Haven and her nephew Chris.
name: Midian

description: Having escaped a kidnapping attempt organized by Leonid and Ash, Nathan and his new friends from Midian are preparing to counterattack. Their target is John Cleverly Cartney, the man who organized the trap against him, and that is going to be elected senator. It is during one of the last rallies of the election campaign that the fate of Nathan and Cartney will cross into an epic and dramatic final act.
name: Il mutante

description: The world is  shocked  by the murder  of a  famous  fashion designer , but  what is worse  is that  to commit  the crime  seems to have been  a boy of  only sixteen years of age , who  wants to communicate  only with  special agent  Never.
name: Legittima difesa

description: Melpomene :  Two baby dealers  are brutally  murdered  by  the  henchmen  of a  drug traffics boss .  A  corrupt cop  decides it's  time to stop  this wave of  barbaric  murders and  sets in motion a  private vendetta .
name: Il prezzo del potere

description: The skeletons of two women are discovered near a scientific setup off  San Cristobal. So Alfa Agency starts a survey that will bring Nathan Never on Quadra, a space mining station home to a sect of  mystics.
name: Sfida nello spazio

description: In the action-packed and playful GEN13: COLLECTED EDITION, a group of teenage adolescents suddenly go from slackers to super-heroes. Unaware that a top secret scientific Gen-Active process had transformed them into super-powered beings, five teenage strangers willingly joined the government's clandestine Project Genesis program. But after learning that the project was actually a covert program to train them as super-powered government agents, the adolescent misfits staged their own escape. Now hunted as fugitives and considered a threat to national security, Burnout, Fairchild, Freefall, Grunge, and Rainmaker know that their only chance for survival is to band together to discover the intertwined secrets of their mysterious past.
name: TPB

description: Mr. Chang, Terpsichore delegate at the General Conference that is taking place on Earth, is killed, and death hangs on the precarious political balance between the colonies and the Earth as the proverbial sword of Damocles... The position that Terpsichore is going to assume, after the murder of his deputy, is crucial in the complex web of alliances to be defined. But what is the role of the mysterious organization of the Praetorians? And can Nathan Never really stop a war that seems inevitable?
name: Il segreto della creatura

description: A new collection presenting the original 5-issue miniseries that launched the phenomenal GENteam and the career of J. Scott Campbell! Aided by former Team Seven leader John Lynch, five teenagers with remarkable power must make their escape from the clutches of Ivana Baiul's array of killers from Internal Operations!
name: TPB

volume.name: Gen 13: Who They Are and How They Came To Be

description: Issue #31
name: IL RICATTO DI SANGUE

description: Issue #10
name: ATROCITÀ IN AMAZZONIA

description:
Everyone's favorite Merc with a Mouth continues hacking and wisecracking his way across the Marvel Universe in this latest volume of riotous, ridiculous and outright reprehensible team-ups!

In Round 1, it's clobberin' time as Deapoolmania runs wild on the Thing! In Round 2, Indiana Deadpool runs afoul of Thor amid Asgard's ruins and learns some treasures are best left undisturbed - particularly the ones containing evil, enormously powerful spirits imprisoned by Odin thousands of years hence. In Round 3, Deadpool and Iron Fist grudgingly team up to stop an ancient and villainous warlord - but Deadpool have to take down Iron Fist, as well, to secure his payday? In Round 4, gaze in horror upon the fiendish experiments inflicted upon Deadpool and Bessie the Vampire Cow by the malevolent Dr. Kilgore in the name of mad science, and bear witness to their terrible revenge! In Round 5, the voices in Deadpool's head hire him to do the dirtiest job of his career, but the mission is endangered when he's trapped in an elevator with the Watcher! In Round 6, Deadpool realizes there's no government bailout for super-powered mercenaries and is forced to do the unthinkable: look for a job!

Luckily, Galactus has a position open in the Herald department. And for the knockout punch: Wolverine, Deadpool and a giant robot!

description:
Marvel U.K.'s first original super hero made his explosive debut in 1976. Now, on his 35th anniversary, Captain Britain's earliest adventures are collected in the United States for the first time!

Witness the legend's beginning as British student Brian Braddock makes a fateful choice between might and right, and becomes Merlin's champion! Experience Captain Britain's first battles as he faces fearsome foes like the Reaver, Hurricane, Dr. Synne, the Mastermind computer, Lord Hawk, Nykonn and the Manipulator. And thrill to his dynamic team-up with U.S. counterpart Captain America as they join forces to battle the Red Skull!

Plus: the debut of Brian's sister, Betsy Braddock - better known today as the X-Men's Psylocke! Never before seen on our shores, these early tales of Marvel U.K.'s original hero are classic British action, presented in the Mighty Marvel Manner!

BIG TIME HITS SPIDER-MAN'S GREATEST ENEMY!

The world's most dangerous felon is in the world's top supermax prison - an institution so secret even the vice president doesn't know it exists. But can any cell contain Norman Osborn? After the events of SIEGE, the former Green Goblin, Iron Patriot and power-mad director of worldwide security isn't allowed to have a toothbrush - and he's surrounded by the world's deadliest criminals.

Lucky for Osborn, they're fans. Rising stars Kelly Sue DeConnick (SIF) and Emma Rios (AMAZING SPIDER-MAN) throw Osborn in the darkest hole the public's never seen! Featuring a bonus story written by Warren Ellis (THUNDERBOLTS)!

description:
To save Thor, Odin places his son into the body of human architect and single father Eric Masterson - and neither of their lives will ever be the same! And after living for months as Thor - facing such threats as Loki, Ulik and the Enchantress - will Masterson be willing to give up his life as a hero once the real Thor returns? It's Thunder God vs. Thunder God, leading to the creation of the new hero: Thunderstrike!
